values:
&nbsp;One of my group mate in the AFM just sms me. She told me that she does not have any marks for the final assignment. Well done, well done. At last you notice, after I try to contact you via sms, phone and uni. website too. Thank god you are meeting the professor tonight. If not, well, lets not talk about it.&nbsp;

I am so very, very tired..... Tired of everything.I mean.... haaaah.... Just tired. I met my brother again today. I seems to meet him everywhere. I saw him in the morning, passing by. Then, in the afternoon when I was in the bookstore for my textbooks.
Heck, my friends who also studies here had never meet me that often. Twice a day is twice too many. But then again, I couldn't do anything. I sign up for writing clinic today. Not too bad, and its just 2 hours per week, which is just one day per week.

A fter this will be the yoga. Ah, well, one step at a time. I guess I am feeling okay right now. Calm and relaxed. Well, I am just waiting for another bad news to come. I don't know what or why, but I have a feeling that other bad things will happen. After all, since when does my life not sucks. I know I sounds like a pessimist, but what else can I do? Do you expect me to be a foolish optimist that believes in everything will be ok in the end?

I don't think so.&nbsp;

&nbsp;Isn't it strange how human change? Sometimes, I ask myself, what have change? Which one have change? Me or others? Do the change that I see in others are caused by me, looking at them differently, or do they change?

But then again, do they actually change? or are they the same? They say that everything change. Everybody change. However, does change happen automatically or do they change because they wanted to be changed?&nbsp;

I am entering university now. I begin to depend on myself and no one. Yet, I realize that now, I have to ask about many things to different people, to strangers. I have to learn to ask, then only, will I be able to grow. Along the way, I also realize that I have been extremely sheltered in life. I am somehow book smart but not street wise. This brought me to my question, is it better to be book smart or street wise?&nbsp;

Each of them have different potential. By being book smart, I will be assured with jobs on a high position. However, how much of that book smart could help me in a real world?&nbsp;

What about being street wise? If I am street wise, I can survive anywhere, anytime. However, what should I do to excell in my career? I would need that book education in my job.&nbsp;

Being book smart and street wise is good. Therefore, everyone should have that book smart and street wise together.&nbsp;
But, I am being a hypocrite. I am telling people to be book smart and street wise, yet I am neither.I do not excell in anything.
